Former Secretary of Homeland Security Tom Ridge, former Deputy National Security Adviser Juan Zarate, and former Homeland Security Adviser Frances Townsend all praise Kirstjen Nielsen's appointment as the new Secretary of Homeland Security. They highlight her experience and expertise in dealing with various threats to national security. Chairman of the Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs Committee Sen. Ron Johnson and Chairman of the House Homeland Security Committee Rep. Mike McCa also express their support for Nielsen, emphasizing her knowledge of the Department of Homeland Security and her background in national security policy decision-making. Senators Steve Daines and Tom Tillis commend her nomination, specifically mentioning her cybersecurity experience.